criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Adults ages 20-70 years;

          -  Body mass index (BMI) ≥ 27 or body fat ≥ 30;

          -  No history of serious diseases associated with heart, liver, kidney, endocrine systems
             or other organs;

          -  No drugs consumption.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  BMI > 35;

          -  Alcoholic;

          -  Un-controlled diabetics;

          -  Stoke in past one year;

          -  High blood pressure;

          -  Mental disease or melancholia;

          -  Pregnancy or breast-feeding a child.
